EQUINE INFLUENZA - INDIA (04): (UTTARAKHAND), UPDATE
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 5 Jun 2009
Source: Horsetalk [edited]
<http://www.horsetalk.co.nz/news/2009/06/028.shtml>


The latest cases of equine influenza in India's long-running battle
against the disease are in the state of Uttaranchal [Uttarakhand].
India, in its latest report on the outbreak to the World Organisation
for Animal Health, reports cases in 5 village locations across the
state.

Worst-affected were the areas of Ukhimath, Gaurikund and Rudraprayag,
which had a total of 114 cases. Case numbers in other villages ranged
from 2 to 24.

The most recent cases include 6 horses that became infected at the
Haridwar police stables.

India has been fighting the outbreak across several states since the
middle of last year [2008].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Susan Baekeland

[India submitted to the OIE its follow-up report No. 5 on this
epizootic, addressing 16 new outbreaks, on 3 Jun 2009; see --
including map -- at
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=8146>.
- Mod.AS]
